               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BORNIE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1060" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1060" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1060" type="surname" value="RIGER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1060" type="given" value="CHRISTIAN"></interp>CHRISTIAN RIGER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at 3, London-buildings, Whitecross-street, on the first-floor. The street floor is usually left open—the landlord does not live there—on 10th April I went out with my wife, about half-past seven o'clock—she fastened the door—we returned about twelve, and found the door broken open, and missed these pictures and other things—they are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1061" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1061" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1061" type="surname" value="RIOBR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1061" type="given" value="ESTHER"></interp>ESTHER RIOBR</persName>
                  </hi>. I went out with my husband, and fastened the door with a key—I came hack, and missed these things.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490409-name-1062" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1062" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1062" type="surname" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490409-name-1062" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>CATHERINE PEARCE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in this house, on the ground-floor. On the night of 10th April, between eight and nine, I saw two boys come out of Mr. Riger's passage—one escaped—I laid hold of the prisoner, and said, "You have been robbing the place"—he said, "Oh, Mrs. Pearce, let me go, I will bring the things back"—I gave him to my husband.</p>
               <p>
